1
00:00:00,890 --> 00:00:02,890
Previously on Fairy Tail:

2
00:00:02,890 --> 00:00:06,590
We beat Brain, and there's 
only one of Oracion Seis left!

3
00:00:06,590 --> 00:00:08,200
That is just a dream.

4
00:00:08,200 --> 00:00:12,330
But we were caught by a trap, 
and Mr. Potato Head was...

5
00:00:12,330 --> 00:00:13,980
That is also a dream.

6
00:00:13,980 --> 00:00:17,440
I know the light that's inside Jellal.

7
00:00:17,440 --> 00:00:19,390
And that, especially, is a dream.

8
00:01:55,540 --> 00:01:56,970
You can still stand?

9
00:01:58,620 --> 00:02:01,470
Just as the rumors say, Erza...

10
00:02:02,760 --> 00:02:04,720
Breaking you will totally 
be worth the effort!

11
00:02:05,930 --> 00:02:09,650
I will stop you and your idiotic goals!

12
00:02:10,780 --> 00:02:11,980
Without fail.

13
00:02:12,910 --> 00:02:17,230
There is no stopping us! We are near!

14
00:02:17,230 --> 00:02:20,150
Caitshelter!

15
00:02:25,390 --> 00:02:26,900
Come to me, Erza.

16
00:02:27,300 --> 00:02:29,350
Or rather, Titania...

17
00:02:29,920 --> 00:02:33,080
Now, show me your true strength.

18
00:02:34,360 --> 00:02:39,020
Although your attacks still 
won't be able to hit me.

19
00:02:42,280 --> 00:02:48,690
Yes, that's right. His magic, 
Reflector, can bend away any attack.

20
00:02:49,090 --> 00:02:51,990
Is there a way to defeat him?

21
00:03:00,330 --> 00:03:01,260
Zero!

22
00:03:08,250 --> 00:03:09,180
So fast!

23
00:03:09,420 --> 00:03:10,250
But...

24
00:03:10,780 --> 00:03:15,170
My Reflector will not be broken, 
no matter how quickly you move!

25
00:03:20,690 --> 00:03:21,590
See?

26
00:03:30,140 --> 00:03:31,680
W-What?

27
00:03:32,910 --> 00:03:34,150
There are two.

28
00:03:35,880 --> 00:03:39,170
There are two weaknesses to your magic.

29
00:03:41,090 --> 00:03:43,110
<i>Two</i> weaknesses?

30
00:03:44,000 --> 00:03:47,120
In just a short time, she...

31
00:03:47,830 --> 00:03:49,140
Weakness number 1:

32
00:03:49,140 --> 00:03:52,850
You may be able to bend magic and objects,

33
00:03:52,850 --> 00:03:56,130
but you are unable to bend human bodies.

34
00:03:57,130 --> 00:04:02,240
If that were not the case, it would have 
been faster to warp my body than my armor.

35
00:04:03,290 --> 00:04:04,150
Am I right?

36
00:04:05,900 --> 00:04:08,760
So, what of it?

37
00:04:18,980 --> 00:04:25,530
Even if that's the case, if I'm being 
serious, I can finish you off with your clothes.

38
00:04:29,620 --> 00:04:31,750
The second weakness: This!

39
00:04:38,080 --> 00:04:39,990
Erza, what are you...

40
00:04:39,990 --> 00:04:42,670
But he said that attacks won't hit him!

41
00:04:54,720 --> 00:04:59,900
While you were bending my armor, 
you dodged my sword normally!

42
00:05:07,020 --> 00:05:10,480
Why didn't you bend the 
path of the sword instead?

43
00:05:11,210 --> 00:05:16,290
The answer: Because you can only bend 
things in one limited area at a time.

44
00:05:16,750 --> 00:05:19,290
The area around yourself, or 
the area around your enemy...

45
00:05:19,290 --> 00:05:21,030
You must choose one or the other.

46
00:05:21,350 --> 00:05:26,710
While you are casting your magic on me, you 
cannot activate Reflector around yourself.

47
00:05:29,000 --> 00:05:31,260
What incredible battle perception!

48
00:05:33,920 --> 00:05:37,630
And this, my Robe of Remoteness,

49
00:05:37,630 --> 00:05:39,770
is flexible armor!

50
00:05:40,000 --> 00:05:42,260
Your magic will not work!

51
00:05:45,930 --> 00:05:50,520
Oh? I guess if you include this 
armor, that's three weaknesses.

52
00:05:52,760 --> 00:05:54,080
Damn it...

53
00:05:54,080 --> 00:05:56,370
I was so close!

54
00:05:56,710 --> 00:05:58,320
This fight is over.

55
00:05:58,760 --> 00:06:00,890
You will surrender without trouble now, yes?

56
00:06:05,430 --> 00:06:07,380
It is already midnight...

57
00:06:07,890 --> 00:06:09,220
It is too late.

58
00:06:09,660 --> 00:06:14,180
If you had let me finish you sooner, 
you could have slept peacefully...

59
00:06:15,550 --> 00:06:18,060
You could have escaped facing the fear!

60
00:06:26,360 --> 00:06:27,160
What's that?

61
00:06:27,420 --> 00:06:28,620
A bell?

62
00:06:29,140 --> 00:06:31,880
It is the bell that chimes midnight.

63
00:06:33,370 --> 00:06:38,860
When it becomes midnight, my 
warping is taken to the extreme!

64
00:06:50,910 --> 00:06:52,770
What is this?

65
00:06:53,580 --> 00:06:56,420
Don't blame me for what's going to happen!

66
00:07:13,530 --> 00:07:16,020
What is this magic?

67
00:07:16,020 --> 00:07:19,960
It's not a Take Over... It's some 
magic power I've never felt before!

68
00:07:21,740 --> 00:07:23,490
Jellal...

69
00:07:29,050 --> 00:07:31,960
Your rule was all a lie...

70
00:07:32,480 --> 00:07:35,720
There was no freedom in the Tower of Heaven.

71
00:07:37,610 --> 00:07:39,510
After the uprising,

72
00:07:39,510 --> 00:07:42,930
I was so scared every night I couldn't sleep!

73
00:07:43,300 --> 00:07:44,230
What?

74
00:07:45,740 --> 00:07:49,440
I see! You all were also... in that tower!

75
00:07:50,960 --> 00:07:53,270
So that's what Cobra was saying...

76
00:07:53,970 --> 00:07:57,280
This is also your sin, Titania!

77
00:07:59,200 --> 00:08:03,580
You averted your eyes for eight years 
from the suffering of your brethren.

78
00:08:04,280 --> 00:08:10,500
And now, at the end, you stand together with 
Jellal, who should be the root of your hatred!

79
00:08:11,300 --> 00:08:16,550
For the people who lost their lives 
for you, it is truly a nightmare.

80
00:08:16,550 --> 00:08:18,390
Don't you think?

81
00:08:23,160 --> 00:08:24,690
Grampa Rob!

82
00:08:25,130 --> 00:08:26,300
Simon!

83
00:08:28,430 --> 00:08:30,610
They are your sins.

84
00:08:30,610 --> 00:08:33,000
You are their nightmare!

85
00:08:33,600 --> 00:08:35,070
You fiend!

86
00:08:42,560 --> 00:08:45,330
Whoa, there... That's pretty cruel.

87
00:08:45,330 --> 00:08:47,710
You laid hands on your allies.

88
00:08:47,710 --> 00:08:49,020
Why, you...

89
00:08:50,690 --> 00:08:51,850
What?

90
00:08:52,890 --> 00:08:55,250
Yes... That's for the best.

91
00:08:55,500 --> 00:08:58,050
Jellal, done in by your hands...

92
00:08:58,390 --> 00:09:00,640
Villain!

93
00:09:11,480 --> 00:09:13,600
Erza!

94
00:09:13,990 --> 00:09:18,990
But wait! Midnight's just begun 
and there's still much more fun!

95
00:09:43,320 --> 00:09:46,120
W-What happened?

96
00:09:46,680 --> 00:09:48,810
I saw him transform into a giant...

97
00:09:51,830 --> 00:09:54,360
My illusion didn't work?!

98
00:09:54,820 --> 00:09:56,030
Illusion?

99
00:09:56,480 --> 00:10:01,430
Did what I saw all happen while 
the bell was still ringing?

100
00:10:01,870 --> 00:10:05,780
Sorry, but magic that affects 
the eyes doesn't work on me.

101
00:10:07,240 --> 00:10:09,310
B-But that's...

102
00:10:09,310 --> 00:10:11,670
I was the most powerful...

103
00:10:12,270 --> 00:10:16,770
I had surpassed my father... I was 
the strongest of the Six Generals...

104
00:10:18,040 --> 00:10:19,810
I couldn't lose to anyone!

105
00:10:20,900 --> 00:10:22,560
The most powerful...

106
00:10:23,240 --> 00:10:24,560
...wizard...

107
00:10:28,090 --> 00:10:33,790
As long as you laugh at people's suffering, 
that goal will remain far out of reach.

108
00:10:39,000 --> 00:10:41,320
My prayer...

109
00:10:46,260 --> 00:10:50,270
I just wanted to be able to sleep...

110
00:10:51,380 --> 00:10:53,360
In a quiet place...

111
00:10:56,460 --> 00:10:57,840
Father...

112
00:11:01,250 --> 00:11:03,650
This... is Erza.

113
00:11:05,690 --> 00:11:10,890
If you never want to be defeated, you 
must first know your own weaknesses.

114
00:11:12,780 --> 00:11:17,270
And also... always be kind.

115
00:11:33,790 --> 00:11:34,740
Natsu!

116
00:11:35,520 --> 00:11:36,630
Damn it!

117
00:11:36,630 --> 00:11:39,720
Look at him tumble, Lucy!

118
00:11:39,720 --> 00:11:43,050
Well, I don't think that's 
the main point here.

119
00:11:45,090 --> 00:11:46,760
Caught ya!

120
00:11:47,890 --> 00:11:51,230
Great going, Natsu! Now, 
beat the crap out of it!

121
00:11:52,350 --> 00:11:54,060
Stop moving around!

122
00:11:55,270 --> 00:11:57,390
Hold it down properly, you dolt!

123
00:11:57,390 --> 00:11:59,620
Try dodging it instead, you jerk!

124
00:12:00,470 --> 00:12:02,750
This battle isn't pretty.

125
00:12:07,200 --> 00:12:10,120
Here we go again! The usual...

126
00:12:10,120 --> 00:12:11,940
The usual over self-consciousness?

127
00:12:11,940 --> 00:12:12,790
No!

128
00:12:12,790 --> 00:12:16,280
The usual "It's such trouble being so cute!"

129
00:12:16,750 --> 00:12:20,670
Natsu, Gray! Lucy broke!

130
00:12:20,670 --> 00:12:24,000
Oh, it's just a kid. Such a disappointment...

131
00:12:24,000 --> 00:12:25,220
A kid?!

132
00:12:25,220 --> 00:12:26,550
Now!

133
00:12:29,730 --> 00:12:31,560
You brats...

134
00:12:33,880 --> 00:12:35,360
Natsu, Gray!

135
00:12:35,360 --> 00:12:37,610
Oh, no! That guy's actually strong!

136
00:12:38,540 --> 00:12:41,990
What's wrong? Is all you got your youth?

137
00:12:41,990 --> 00:12:44,720
Youth alone isn't going to beat me!

138
00:12:44,720 --> 00:12:47,920
You young'ns always showin' 
off your young selves, you!

139
00:12:47,920 --> 00:12:50,920
I think he might be a bit 
self-conscious about his age...

140
00:12:50,920 --> 00:12:51,740
Aye...

141
00:12:53,200 --> 00:12:54,450
And what?

142
00:12:54,450 --> 00:12:56,060
Right on the mark, huh?

143
00:12:56,060 --> 00:12:57,870
No, I think it's something else.

144
00:13:01,640 --> 00:13:03,710
Incredible...

145
00:13:03,710 --> 00:13:09,030
All six... All Six Generals are wiped out!

146
00:13:15,680 --> 00:13:18,270
No, this is bad! Very bad!

147
00:13:18,270 --> 00:13:20,310
He is coming!

148
00:13:20,910 --> 00:13:22,390
What's he saying?

149
00:13:22,390 --> 00:13:23,520
"He"?

150
00:13:23,520 --> 00:13:25,580
There's someone else?

151
00:13:25,580 --> 00:13:27,320
Don't tell me the eighth?

152
00:13:47,660 --> 00:13:49,430
What are you talking about?

153
00:13:49,430 --> 00:13:50,950
He's juicing like crazy!

154
00:13:50,950 --> 00:13:52,270
You mean sweat!

155
00:13:52,270 --> 00:13:53,870
Brain...

156
00:13:54,860 --> 00:13:57,730
If you're talking about him, Jura beat him.

157
00:13:57,730 --> 00:13:59,430
No...

158
00:13:59,430 --> 00:14:03,730
Brain has another personality.

159
00:14:04,570 --> 00:14:09,810
There is the front face, codenamed 
Brain, who holds so much knowledge.

160
00:14:09,810 --> 00:14:16,250
And then there is the back face, codenamed 
Zero, who loves nothing but destruction.

161
00:14:16,920 --> 00:14:18,810
Loves destruction?

162
00:14:19,270 --> 00:14:20,580
Zero?

163
00:14:20,580 --> 00:14:24,500
Due to his overwhelming, evil magical powers,

164
00:14:24,500 --> 00:14:29,340
Brain sealed that existence 
away himself with six keys.

165
00:14:30,680 --> 00:14:33,600
And those are... Oracion Seis!

166
00:14:33,600 --> 00:14:35,500
Exactly.

167
00:14:35,500 --> 00:14:39,980
And when the Six Generals fall, and 
their Body Link magic is broken,

168
00:14:40,230 --> 00:14:46,530
the personality of Zero will 
be reborn once again...

169
00:14:49,000 --> 00:14:50,900
This sounds like fun!

170
00:15:00,610 --> 00:15:03,330
Welcome back, Master Zero!

171
00:15:06,460 --> 00:15:07,480
Master?

172
00:15:08,140 --> 00:15:12,290
Klodoa, it seems things have 
gotten quite interesting.

173
00:15:12,540 --> 00:15:15,380
Even that Midnight was beaten?

174
00:15:15,910 --> 00:15:17,850
I-I truly apologize!

175
00:15:17,850 --> 00:15:22,650
Although, it sure has been a 
while, to have this feeling...

176
00:15:22,650 --> 00:15:25,610
To have this body... This voice!

177
00:15:26,140 --> 00:15:27,920
This magic!

178
00:15:27,920 --> 00:15:30,200
It all brings me back...

179
00:15:31,810 --> 00:15:33,390
I'll handle the rest.

180
00:15:33,740 --> 00:15:35,500
Stand back, Klodoa.

181
00:15:47,560 --> 00:15:49,000
You little brats...

182
00:15:49,580 --> 00:15:53,250
You sure made a mess out of my guild.

183
00:15:54,440 --> 00:15:58,760
As its master, I will make you pay for that.

184
00:16:00,140 --> 00:16:05,330
He's... the guildmaster of Oracion Seis?

185
00:16:05,330 --> 00:16:06,360
Zero!

186
00:16:10,470 --> 00:16:13,030
The ground is shaking from his magic power?

187
00:16:13,280 --> 00:16:15,990
Gettin' fired up, Natsu?

188
00:16:15,990 --> 00:16:19,700
I've never felt magic power this nasty!

189
00:16:22,080 --> 00:16:23,290
That's right...

190
00:16:23,820 --> 00:16:31,210
I'll start by erasing this baldy 
who hurt this body's Brain!

191
00:16:36,030 --> 00:16:39,720
You're gonna attack someone 
who can't even move?

192
00:16:40,970 --> 00:16:43,430
What nonsense...

193
00:16:47,000 --> 00:16:50,380
My shield is being broken, just like that?

194
00:16:54,740 --> 00:16:55,980
Old dude!

195
00:16:55,980 --> 00:16:56,840
Gray!

196
00:16:57,870 --> 00:17:01,640
Whether he can move or not 
isn't much of a difference.

197
00:17:01,640 --> 00:17:05,580
As long as it has form, it's 
just as fun to destroy!

198
00:17:09,530 --> 00:17:10,960
Why, you...

199
00:17:14,140 --> 00:17:16,030
Oh, no!

200
00:17:18,860 --> 00:17:20,800
W-What'll we do?

201
00:17:21,400 --> 00:17:24,010
My body's... frozen stiff...

202
00:17:30,450 --> 00:17:31,820
I'm scared!

203
00:17:54,800 --> 00:17:58,250
Impressive, Master Zero! 
Excellent work as always!

204
00:17:58,250 --> 00:18:02,260
Defeating these annoying 
brats like they were nothing!

205
00:18:04,340 --> 00:18:06,980
But they still live.

206
00:18:08,140 --> 00:18:11,080
You're still alive, aren't you?

207
00:18:11,600 --> 00:18:13,050
Stand up.

208
00:18:13,440 --> 00:18:16,870
You still have form!

209
00:18:34,660 --> 00:18:35,750
Does it hurt?

210
00:18:36,190 --> 00:18:38,500
No, I'm fine...

211
00:18:39,080 --> 00:18:40,330
I apologize.

212
00:18:41,300 --> 00:18:44,520
I was in too much of a hurry to stop Nirvana.

213
00:18:45,680 --> 00:18:50,100
That wound... And the fact you'd used 
up nearly all your magic power...

214
00:18:50,490 --> 00:18:54,290
You were barely even able to 
stand, weren't you, Jellal?

215
00:18:55,730 --> 00:19:03,200
No, it's okay. It doesn't change the fact 
that it was I who undid the seal on Nirvana.

216
00:19:04,210 --> 00:19:05,780
We must hurry and stop it.

217
00:19:08,420 --> 00:19:09,530
I wonder for how long...

218
00:19:11,650 --> 00:19:18,030
How long will I be able to remain 
anchored at this harbor known as battle?

219
00:19:36,900 --> 00:19:38,270
He's gone.

220
00:19:38,270 --> 00:19:40,950
Where are you, Jellal?

221
00:19:42,150 --> 00:19:45,390
Wendy, I'm at my limit. Let me rest a bit.

222
00:19:45,660 --> 00:19:46,280
Sure!

223
00:19:47,030 --> 00:19:49,930
I'm sorry for pushing you, Carla.

224
00:19:49,930 --> 00:19:51,210
It's fine.

225
00:19:56,660 --> 00:19:58,800
I remember that mountain.

226
00:19:59,460 --> 00:20:01,590
We're almost there.

227
00:20:01,830 --> 00:20:06,800
Sheesh. But this ancient city is huge!

228
00:20:07,360 --> 00:20:08,790
What'll we do?

229
00:20:08,790 --> 00:20:12,640
It's no use... No matter how 
much we look, we won't find him!

230
00:20:12,940 --> 00:20:15,690
You getting weak-knees isn't going to help.

231
00:20:15,690 --> 00:20:17,980
At this rate, Caitshelter will be...

232
00:20:17,980 --> 00:20:19,230
I know that!

233
00:20:19,670 --> 00:20:22,630
I know, but what should I do?

234
00:20:23,140 --> 00:20:25,380
Decide on one thing!

235
00:20:26,730 --> 00:20:28,650
Do you want to see Jellal?

236
00:20:28,890 --> 00:20:31,680
Do you want Jellal to stop this thing?

237
00:20:31,680 --> 00:20:35,000
If you chase two rabbits at 
once, you won't catch either!

238
00:20:36,640 --> 00:20:38,960
Right. We have to stop it.

239
00:20:38,960 --> 00:20:41,510
Right now, we have to stop Nirvana!

240
00:20:44,020 --> 00:20:48,070
Don't think about other 
things, and keep searching.

241
00:20:48,070 --> 00:20:49,010
Right!

242
00:20:53,270 --> 00:20:56,550
We have to stop it! Right 
now, we have to stop it!

243
00:21:05,900 --> 00:21:09,870
I can see it! I can see it! 
I can see it, Master Zero!

244
00:21:09,870 --> 00:21:12,170
Thank you for waiting! I can see it!

245
00:21:12,170 --> 00:21:16,130
There is it! I can see Caitshelter!

246
00:21:16,500 --> 00:21:21,810
That's the guild of the race that 
has sealed Nirvana for an eternity!

247
00:21:22,750 --> 00:21:29,740
All we have to do is destroy them, and 
then Nirvana can never be sealed again!

248
00:21:29,740 --> 00:21:32,570
Alrighty then!

249
00:21:32,570 --> 00:21:34,220
This is stupid.

250
00:21:35,950 --> 00:21:38,520
You heard me, Klodoa.

251
00:21:43,750 --> 00:21:46,190
What, Master Zero?

252
00:21:49,650 --> 00:21:54,330
Destruction! All I want to do is destroy!

253
00:21:54,330 --> 00:21:57,950
Anything and everything!

254
00:21:57,950 --> 00:22:00,590
This will be my first shot!

255
00:22:00,590 --> 00:22:05,090
There's no reason. Until it no 
longer has a form left to destroy!

256
00:22:10,590 --> 00:22:15,430
Nirvana, fire!

257
00:23:55,820 --> 00:23:58,520
Natsu, do you know about Pegasus?

258
00:23:58,520 --> 00:24:01,620
Sure... It's the thing that Hibiki's 
guildmark is a picture of.

259
00:24:01,620 --> 00:24:05,040
Aye! It's supposed to be a winged horse!

260
00:24:05,040 --> 00:24:08,950
It's not just snakes, but 
horses with wings, too!

261
00:24:08,950 --> 00:24:11,010
My character's being ripped 
off right and left!

262
00:24:11,010 --> 00:24:13,500
Is having wings all the rage lately?

263
00:24:13,890 --> 00:24:16,910
